{"title_page": "2003\u201304 Gen\u00e7lerbirli\u011fi S.K. season", "text_new": "{{Orphan|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{Infobox football club season\n| club             = [[Gen\u00e7lerbirli\u011fi S.K.]]\n| season           = 2003\u201304\n| chairman         = \n| manager          = {{flagicon|TUR}} [[Ersun Yanal]]\n| league           = [[S\u00fcper Lig]]\n| league result    = [[2003\u201304 S\u00fcper Lig|10th]]\n| league topscorer = [[Souleymane Youla]] (16)\n| season topscorer = \n| cup1             = [[Turkish Cup]]\n| cup1 result      = [[2003\u201304 Turkish Cup|Runners-up]]\n| cup2             = [[UEFA Europa League|UEFA Cup]]\n| cup2 result      = [[2003\u201304 UEFA Cup#Fourth round|Fourth round]]\n| prevseason       = [[2002\u201303 Gen\u00e7lerbirli\u011fi S.K. season|2002\u201303]]\n| nextseason       = [[2004\u201305 Gen\u00e7lerbirli\u011fi S.K. season|2004\u201305]]\n}}\nDuring the '''2003\u201304''' Turkish football season, Gen\u00e7lerbirli\u011fi S.K. competed in the S\u00fcper Lig.\n\n==Season summary==\nGen\u00e7lerbirli\u011fi reached the fourth round of the UEFA Cup before being knocked out by eventual runners-up Valencia.\n\n==First-team squad==\n:''Squad at end of season''\n{{fs start}}\n{{Fs player|no=3|nat=BEL|pos=DF|name=[[Filip Daems]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=5|nat=EGY|pos=DF|name=[[Abdel-Zaher El-Saqua]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=6|nat=TUR|pos=DF|name=[[Erkan \u00d6zbey]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=7|nat=TUR|pos=MF|name=[[B\u00fclent Ak\u0131n]]<ref group=notes>Ak\u0131n was born in [[Brussels]], [[Belgium]].</ref>}}\n{{Fs player|no=8|nat=TUR|pos=FW|name=[[Mustafa \u00d6zkan]]<ref group=notes>\u00d6zkan was born in [[Forchheim]], [[West Germany]] (now [[Germany]]).</ref>}}\n{{Fs player|no=9|nat=TUR|pos=FW|name=Bege\u00e7arslan Ali Cansun}}\n{{Fs player|no=10|nat=TUR|pos=MF|name=[[Nihat Ba\u015ft\u00fcrk]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=11|nat=GUI|pos=FW|name=[[Souleymane Youla]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=12|nat=DRC|pos=MF|name=[[Marcel Kimemba Mbayo]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=14|nat=TUR|pos=DF